# Card Duel Project

A browser-based fantasy card game interface created as a long-term frontend portfolio project.

## About The Project

Card Duel Project is a personal frontend development project focused on building a clean, responsive and scalable card game UI from scratch.

The project currently focuses on creating a strong UI foundation and well-organized architecture before implementing full game logic and React integration.

The main purpose of this project is to:

- improve frontend development skills,
- practice modern HTML & CSS architecture,
- learn scalable project organization,
- prepare the application for JavaScript and React implementation,
- document continuous learning progress through real development workflow.

## Current Tech Stack

- HTML5
- CSS3
- Git & GitHub
- Visual Studio Code

## Current Features

### UI Layout
- Split battlefield structure:
  - enemy side,
  - center action area,
  - player side.

### Player Interface
- Player and enemy panels,
- HP and Mana indicators,
- responsive stat containers.

### Game Board
- Interactive card slots,
- hover animations,
- prepared structure for future card rendering.

### Visual Design
- Dark fantasy-inspired theme,
- gradient background,
- glassmorphism-inspired UI elements,
- smooth hover transitions,
- custom typography using Google Fonts (`Cinzel`).

### Code Organization
- semantic HTML structure,
- BEM naming convention,
- modular CSS sections,
- scalable layout prepared for future React components.

## Planned Features

### JavaScript Features
- Full turn-based game logic,
- card placement system,
- mana system,
- health system,
- game states,
- win/lose conditions.

### UI Improvements
- Card animations,
- drag & drop mechanics,
- responsive mobile layout,
- visual effects,
- sound effects.

### React Migration
The project is intentionally being structured to allow smooth migration into React in the future.

Planned React features:
- reusable components,
- state management,
- dynamic rendering,
- component-based architecture.

